# Compiler Options & Development Notes

## Environment Variables Required for Production
- APP_PASSWORD: bcrypt hashed password for API authentication
- NODE_ENV: production/development
- Database: SQLite file (ledger.db) will be auto-created on first run

## Key Technical Decisions
- NO TypeScript (sticking to JavaScript ES modules per requirements)
- Currency stored as INTEGER cents (avoiding floating point precision issues)
- SQLite with WAL mode for better concurrent access in development
- bcrypt with 12 salt rounds for password hashing

## Architecture Patterns
- Separation of concerns: logic/db/routes in separate directories
- Modularity: Depreciation calculations isolated from API endpoints
- Event-driven: React state updates trigger API calls and re-renders

## Pending Considerations (if future development)
- Error handling can be more granular (custom error classes)
- Rate limiting for API endpoints (production hardening)
- Input validation could use a schema library (joi, yup)
- Database migrations system if schema changes needed
- Logging system (winston, pino) for production monitoring
- Caching layer (Redis) if performance becomes bottleneck

## UI Framework Notes
- Tailwind CSS with custom utilities (extend config)
- Mobile-first responsive design (320px+ breakpoints)
- PWA manifest and service worker placeholders in place
- Minimal animations/transitions for iOS/Android native feel

## Deployment Ready Features
- Multi-stage Dockerfile (React build -> Express + Nginx)
- docker-compose.yml with Traefik labels ready
- Environment variable driven configuration
- Health check endpoints (/health)